article.headline: Colgate 68, Bucknell 57
article.story: HAMILTON, N.Y. -- Alex Woodhouse scored all 13 of his points in the second half to lead Colgate to a 68-57 over Bucknell on Wednesday night. Colgate (7-14, 3-5 Patriot League) snapped a three-game losing streak as Bucknell (5-17, 2-6) remained winless in 13 road games. Woodhouse added eight rebounds and five blocked shots to the Colgate attack, freshman guard Anthony Hill scored a career-high 14 points, and Mike Venezia and Yaw Gyawu had 10 points apiece. Patrick Behan led the Bison with 18 points, Justin Castleberry added 13, and Bryan Cohen 11. Bucknell led 26-23 at halftime, but Colgate scored 13 straight points early in the second half to take command. Woodhouse had four points to key the spurt, which Venezia started with a deep 3-pointer. Colgate made 13-of-16 free throws in the final 4 minutes after Bucknell cut the lead to single digits.
